  <h2 class="section-heading" id="action-servers">6.1 Action Servers</h2>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">6.1.1 Creating Action Servers</h3>
  <p>Create a new node for the appropriate language in your workspace. Include the following code snippets <strong>in the constructor of your node class to create a server.</strong></p>

  <div class="param-list">
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-var-inline">[action_server_variable_name]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">: the name of the member variable that will store the action server attribute.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-type-inline">[action_type]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">: the action service type to which the action server &amp; action clients use.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-generic-inline">[action_name]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">: the name of the action provided by the action server.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[action_request_callback_function]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">: a callback (member) function that is called once a request is received by an action client.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[action_cancel_callback_function]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">: a callback (member) function that is called when the action is canceled by an action client.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[action_accepted_callback_function]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">: a callback (member) function that is called when the action request is accepted (usually to start the execution of the action, <strong>which is handled by a separate member function <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline"">[handle_execution_function]</code></strong>).</span>
    </div>
  </div>

