  <h3 class="subsection-heading">6.1.2 Handling Action Client Requests</h3>
  <p>This is the first callback function that will be executed once a request is received. This is mainly used to verify whether the goal of the action is feasible and thus can be executed safely.</p>
  <blockquote>
    <strong class="ph-generic-inline">uuid:</strong> A unique identifier for a specific goal request (16 byte value). This is used to determine which action client sent the request, and can be used to perform queuing or prioritized scheduling.
  </blockquote>

