  <h4 class="subsection-heading">6.1.2.2 C++</h4>
  <CodeBlock code={cppGoalReqCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppGoalReqCustom} />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">6.1.3 Handling Cancel Requests</h3>
  <p>This will be called if ever an action client sends a cancel request. This function is meant to be used to <strong>evaluate whether cancellation is feasible</strong>. The execution function <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[handle_execution_function]</code> is where the action is truly canceled, while <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[action_cancel_callback_function]</code> only forwards the cancellation request to the execution function.</p>

