  <h3 class="subsection-heading">6.1.4 Executing Actions, Providing Feedback &amp; Returning Results</h3>
  <p><code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[action_accepted_callback_function]</code> is called once the action request is accepted. This function is used to start the execution of the action.</p>
  <p><code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[handle_execution_function]</code>: the member variable that will run on a separate thread which actually runs the action.</p>

  <h4 class="subsection-heading">6.1.4.1 Python</h4>
  <p>In RCLPy, there is only one function needed for <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[action_accepted_callback_function]</code> &amp; <code class="param-name ph-fn-inline">[handle_execution_function]</code>; execution is handled automatically in an asynchronous manner.</p>
