  <h3 class="subsection-heading">6.2.3 Sending an Asynchronous Request from a Client to a Server</h3>
  <p>A node sending an asynchronous request can continue performing operations until a response is received. <strong>It is advised but not necessary to wrap the following in a function (that can be called when you want to call an action).</strong> Include the following code into your node class.</p>
